# Project Setup Conventions

Project-wide conventions for EstateHero component library.

## Import Order

Follow this strict import order in all files:

```tsx
// 1. React
import * as React from "react";
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

// 2. Base UI components
import { Button as BaseButton } from "@base-ui-components/react/Button";
import { Input as BaseInput } from "@base-ui-components/react/Input";

// 3. Third-party libraries
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { clsx } from "clsx";

// 4. Local components (absolute imports)
import { IconContainer } from "@/components/ui/icon-container";
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge";

// 5. Utils
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

// 6. Types (if separate file)
import type { ComponentProps } from "./types";

// 7. Styles (if any)
import "./custom-styles.css";
```

### Import Grouping

- Separate groups with blank lines
- Sort alphabetically within groups
- Use absolute imports for internal modules

## File Naming Conventions

### Components

```
kebab-case for files and folders
PascalCase for component names
```

Examples:
- Folder: `icon-container/`
- Component file: `icon-container.tsx`
- Component name: `IconContainer`
- Story file: `icon-container.stories.tsx`
- Types file: `icon-container.types.ts` (if needed)

### Other Files

```
kebab-case for utility files
PascalCase for component/class files
lowercase for config files
```

Examples:
- `utils.ts`
- `cn.ts`
- `tailwind.config.ts`
- `globals.css`
- `.eslintrc.json`

